INSERT INTO `blog_posts` (`postID`, `postTitle`, `image`, `postSlug`, `postDesc`, `postCont`, `postDate`, `postTags`) VALUES
	(1, 'WHAT FOODS ARE GOOD FOR A POST-GYM WORKOUT', 'images.jpg', 'what-foods-are-good-for-a-post-gym-workout', '<p>When you push yourself through a tough workout, you&rsquo;re not actually becoming fitter. What you&rsquo;re doing is stressing your body and priming it to gro...</p>', '<p><img class="blog-post__image" src="https://ne-media-cdn.puregym.com/media/792621/15may_lf_eggscerealorfruit.jpg?quality=80&amp;mode=pad&amp;width=970" alt="image" /></p>\r\n<div class="static-html static-html--blog">\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div class="row clearfix">\r\n<div class="col-md-12 column">\r\n<div>\r\n<p class="Body">When you push yourself through a tough workout, you&rsquo;re not actually becoming fitter. What you&rsquo;re doing is stressing your body and priming it to grow and adapt, in response. If you want to enjoy the best fitness results possible, you&rsquo;ve got to give your body sufficient rest and nutrition to grow and recover after each workout.</p>\r\n<p class="Body">Post-workout nutrition is the start of the recovery and strengthening process, and what you choose to eat matters.</p>\r\n<h3 class="Body">HERE ARE A FEW SUGGESTIONS ON POST-WORKOUT NUTRITION:</h3>\r\n<h4 class="Body">SIMPLE SUGAR SNACKS</h4>\r\n<p class="Body">When you do a high-intensity training session, you&rsquo;ll burn through your body&rsquo;s glycogen stores. Glycogen is the stored form of carbohydrate that your body keeps locked up in your muscles and liver for an emergency.</p>\r\n<p class="Body">During anaerobic exercises, such as sprint training or explosive lifting for more than a few reps, your muscle glycogen is utilised as fuel. If you run out of muscle glycogen, you&rsquo;ll &ldquo;hit the wall&rdquo;, meaning your muscles will lock up and you won&rsquo;t be able to perform.</p>\r\n<p class="Body">Training with insufficient glycogen stores may lead to muscle breakdown,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/7380688/">according to research</a>. But replenishing glycogen after a workout is just as crucial as topping it up beforehand.</p>\r\n<p class="Body">Right after working out,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/9694422/">your body can replenish its glycogen stores at an accelerated rate</a>. Focus on getting in some fast-digesting carbs immediately post-workout but bear in mind portion control and having these moderately.</p>\r\n<p class="Body">Example foods&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>â— &nbsp;&nbsp; White rice/ pasta</p>\r\n<p>â— &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Banana</p>\r\n<p>â— &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Orange juice</p>\r\n<p>â— &nbsp;&nbsp; Coca-cola</p>\r\n<p>â—&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ice cream</p>\r\n<p>â—&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Milk chocolate</p>\r\n<p>â—&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cookies</p>\r\n<p>â— &nbsp;&nbsp; Protein and carb combos</p>\r\n<p class="Body">There is&nbsp;<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/16775553">some research</a>&nbsp;showing evidence that eating protein after a workout, along with carbs, boosts glycogen synthesis significantly.</p>\r\n<p class="Body">Post-workout meals combining protein and carbs will likely also provide a hefty dose of calories and micronutrients to kickstart the recovery process.</p>\r\n<p class="Body">Example foods:</p>\r\n<p class="Body">â— &nbsp;&nbsp; Peanut butter on whole grain toast</p>\r\n<p class="Body">â— &nbsp;&nbsp; Chicken, vegetable and rice</p>\r\n<p class="Body">â—&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Spaghetti Bolognese</p>\r\n<p class="Body">â—&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tuna pasta bake</p>\r\n<p class="Body">â—&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bean stew</p>\r\n<h4 class="Body">SIMPLE LEAN PROTEIN</h4>\r\n<p class="Body">There&rsquo;s an old idea that immediately after doing exercise, there&rsquo;s a powerful &ldquo;anabolic window&rdquo; that opens up. According to the theory, any protein eaten during this period will significantly boost your body&rsquo;s ability to pack on new muscle tissue.</p>\r\n<p class="Body">The research findings on this subject are a bit contradictory and uncertain. A 2013 review published in the Journal of the International Society of Sports Nutrition notes that some reasons for the uncertainty might include flawed study design, including some researchers failing to account for the effects of pre-workout meals.</p>\r\n<p class="Body">Some studies have, however, found&nbsp;<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3577439/">significant anabolic benefits associated with protein</a>consumption immediately after a workout.</p>\r\n<p class="Body">To enjoy these potential benefits, it might be a good idea to focus on low-fat protein sources, as fat slows the process of digestion.</p>\r\n<p class="Body">Example foods:</p>\r\n<p class="Body">â—&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Whey protein powder</p>\r\n<p class="Body">â— &nbsp;&nbsp; Chicken breast</p>\r\n<p class="Body">â—&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Lean beef steak</p>\r\n<p class="Body">â—&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Beans and lentils</p>\r\n<p class="Body">â— &nbsp;&nbsp; Low-fat yoghurt (e.g. Skyr)</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '2019-01-18 22:48:35', 'nutrition'),
	(2, 'BÃ­ quyáº¿t cÃ³ bá»™ ngá»±c cÄƒng trÃ²n quyáº¿n rÅ© khÃ´ng cáº§n pháº«u thuáº­t', 'bi-quyet-co-bo-nguc-cang-tron-quyen-ru-khong-can-phau-thuat(8).jpg', 'bi-quyet-co-bo-nguc-cang-tron-quyen-ru-khong-can-phau-thuat', '<p>Äá»ƒ c&oacute; Ä‘Æ°á»£c bá»™ ngá»±c cÄƒng tr&ograve;n quyáº¿n rÅ©, báº¡n h&atilde;y táº­p b&agrave;i tá»‘t nháº¥t cho v&ograve;ng má»™t ta tr&ograve;n m&agrave; kh&ocirc;ng cáº§n pháº«u thuáº­t.</p>', '<div class="thecontent">\r\n<h2>Äá»ƒ c&oacute; Ä‘Æ°á»£c bá»™ ngá»±c cÄƒng tr&ograve;n quyáº¿n rÅ©, báº¡n h&atilde;y táº­p&nbsp;b&agrave;i tá»‘t nháº¥t cho v&ograve;ng má»™t ta tr&ograve;n m&agrave; kh&ocirc;ng cáº§n pháº«u thuáº­t.</h2>\r\n<p><img src="http://blogthehinh.net/app/webroot/uploads/images/10/2017/12/11/510/bi-quyet-co-bo-nguc-cang-tron-quyen-ru-khong-can-phau-thuat(8).jpg" alt="B&iacute; quyáº¿t c&oacute; bá»™ ngá»±c cÄƒng tr&ograve;n quyáº¿n rÅ© kh&ocirc;ng cáº§n pháº«u thuáº­t" /></p>\r\n<h3><strong>Äá»™ng t&aacute;c&nbsp;n&eacute;m b&oacute;ng Medicine Ball</strong><br /><img src="http://blogthehinh.net/app/webroot/uploads/images/10/2017/12/11/510/bi-quyet-co-bo-nguc-cang-tron-quyen-ru-khong-can-phau-thuat(7).jpg" alt="B&iacute; quyáº¿t c&oacute; bá»™ ngá»±c cÄƒng tr&ograve;n quyáº¿n rÅ© kh&ocirc;ng cáº§n pháº«u thuáº­t" /><br />Äá»™ng t&aacute;c n&eacute;m b&oacute;ng n&agrave;y gi&uacute;p ngáº·c cÄƒng tr&ograve;n hÆ¡n</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Hai tay giá»¯ b&oacute;ng Medicine ball</li>\r\n<li>Äá»©ng hai ch&acirc;n rá»™ng báº±ng vai</li>\r\n<li>HÆ¡i cong hai gá»‘i</li>\r\n<li>N&acirc;ng b&oacute;ng qua Ä‘áº§u.</li>\r\n<li>N&eacute;m xuá»‘ng s&agrave;n trÆ°á»›c ngÆ°á»i c&agrave;ng máº¡nh c&agrave;ng tá»‘t.</li>\r\n<li>Láº·p láº¡i 3 v&aacute;n, 20 láº§n láº·p Ä‘á»ƒ cáº£m nháº­n sá»± Ä‘á»‘t ch&aacute;y&nbsp; má»¡.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Äá»™ng t&aacute;c&nbsp;Y-Press</strong></h3>\r\n<p><img src="http://blogthehinh.net/app/webroot/uploads/images/10/2017/12/11/510/bi-quyet-co-bo-nguc-cang-tron-quyen-ru-khong-can-phau-thuat(6).jpg" alt="B&iacute; quyáº¿t c&oacute; bá»™ ngá»±c cÄƒng tr&ograve;n quyáº¿n rÅ© kh&ocirc;ng cáº§n pháº«u thuáº­t" /></p>\r\n<p>Äá»™ng t&aacute;c n&agrave;y t&aacute;c Ä‘á»™ng v&agrave;o c&aacute;c cÆ¡ ngá»±c tr&ecirc;n gi&uacute;p ngÆ°á»i táº­p c&oacute; v&oacute;c d&aacute;ng ngÆ°á»i khá»e máº¡nh hÆ¡n. H&atilde;y táº­p Ä‘á»™ng t&aacute;c n&agrave;y vá»›i táº¡ Ä‘á»ƒ gi&uacute;p cÆ¡ th&ecirc;m dáº»o dai hÆ¡n.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Äá»©ng tháº³ng hai ch&acirc;n rá»™ng báº±ng h&ocirc;ng.</li>\r\n<li>Hai tay giá»¯ hai táº¡ tay ngang vai, l&ograve;ng b&agrave;n tay hÆ°á»›ng vá» ph&iacute;a trÆ°á»›c.</li>\r\n<li>Hai tay duá»—i tháº³ng v&agrave; n&acirc;ng qua Ä‘áº§u táº¡o h&igrave;nh chá»¯ Y.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Äá»™ng t&aacute;c&nbsp;h&iacute;t Ä‘áº¥t (má»™t ná»­a náº¿u cáº§n)</strong></h3>\r\n<p><img src="http://blogthehinh.net/app/webroot/uploads/images/10/2017/12/11/510/bi-quyet-co-bo-nguc-cang-tron-quyen-ru-khong-can-phau-thuat(5).jpg" alt="B&iacute; quyáº¿t c&oacute; bá»™ ngá»±c cÄƒng tr&ograve;n quyáº¿n rÅ© kh&ocirc;ng cáº§n pháº«u thuáº­t" /></p>\r\n<p>Äá»™ng t&aacute;c káº¿t há»£p n&agrave;y gi&uacute;p x&acirc;y dá»±ng nhiá»u v&ugrave;ng cÆ¡. Báº±ng c&aacute;ch sá»­ dá»¥ng 1 b&agrave;i táº­p káº¿t há»£p nhÆ° Ä‘á»™ng t&aacute;c h&iacute;t Ä‘áº¥t cÆ¡ báº£n, báº¡n sáº½ tháº¥y ngay hiá»‡u quáº£ á»Ÿ v&ugrave;ng ngá»±c.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Báº¯t Ä‘áº§u báº±ng tÆ° tháº¿ náº±m sáº¥p tr&ecirc;n tháº£m.</li>\r\n<li>Äáº·t hai tay hai b&ecirc;n ngá»±c.</li>\r\n<li>N&acirc;ng th&acirc;n ngÆ°á»i l&ecirc;n táº¡o tÆ° tháº¿ h&iacute;t Ä‘áº¥t hoáº·c ná»­a h&iacute;t Ä‘áº¥t báº±ng c&aacute;ch cong gá»‘i (Ä‘áº·t má»™t b&agrave;n ch&acirc;n ch&eacute;o l&ecirc;n máº¯t c&aacute; ch&acirc;n kia).</li>\r\n<li>CÄƒng cÆ¡ bá»¥ng v&agrave; tá»« tá»« háº¡ th&acirc;n ngÆ°á»i tá»« tá»« xuá»‘ng (trong 3-4 nhá»‹p thá»Ÿ).</li>\r\n<li>Äáº©y ngÆ°á»i l&ecirc;n v&agrave; láº·p láº¡i c&agrave;ng nhiá»u láº§n c&agrave;ng tá»‘t.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Äá»™ng t&aacute;c&nbsp;Ä‘áº©y táº¡ tr&ecirc;n gháº¿ táº­p</strong></h3>\r\n<p><img src="http://blogthehinh.net/app/webroot/uploads/images/10/2017/12/11/510/bi-quyet-co-bo-nguc-cang-tron-quyen-ru-khong-can-phau-thuat(4).jpg" alt="B&iacute; quyáº¿t c&oacute; bá»™ ngá»±c cÄƒng tr&ograve;n quyáº¿n rÅ© kh&ocirc;ng cáº§n pháº«u thuáº­t" /></p>\r\n<p>Äá»™ng t&aacute;c n&agrave;y c&oacute; t&aacute;c Ä‘á»™ng ráº¥t tá»‘t cho nhá»¯ng phá»¥ ná»¯ Ä‘ang muá»‘n l&agrave;m sÄƒn cháº¯c c&aacute;c cÆ¡ ngá»±c. B&agrave;i táº­p n&agrave;y c&oacute; thá»ƒ thá»±c hiá»‡n vá»›i má»™t táº¡ tay, táº¡ Ä‘Æ¡n hoáº·c b&oacute;ng thá»ƒ dá»¥c.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Náº±m ngá»­a lÆ°ng tr&ecirc;n b&oacute;ng hoáº·c gháº¿ táº­p.</li>\r\n<li>Hai gá»‘i cong 1 g&oacute;c 90 Ä‘á»™ vá»›i s&agrave;n</li>\r\n<li>Báº¯t Ä‘áº§u báº±ng hai táº¡ tay á»Ÿ b&ecirc;n ngá»±c.</li>\r\n<li>Duá»—i hai táº¡ tay qua Ä‘áº§u, duá»—i tháº³ng hai c&aacute;nh tay. (Giá»¯ trong 3 gi&acirc;y)</li>\r\n<li>Háº¡ tháº¥p hai tay xuá»‘ng ngá»±c v&agrave; láº·p láº¡i.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Äá»™ng t&aacute;c&nbsp;nh&uacute;n gháº¿</strong></h3>\r\n<p><img src="http://blogthehinh.net/app/webroot/uploads/images/10/2017/12/11/510/bi-quyet-co-bo-nguc-cang-tron-quyen-ru-khong-can-phau-thuat(3).jpg" alt="B&iacute; quyáº¿t c&oacute; bá»™ ngá»±c cÄƒng tr&ograve;n quyáº¿n rÅ© kh&ocirc;ng cáº§n pháº«u thuáº­t" /></p>\r\n<p>Äá»™ng t&aacute;c n&agrave;y kh&ocirc;ng chá»‰ t&aacute;c Ä‘á»™ng v&agrave;o cÆ¡ tam Ä‘áº§u m&agrave; c&ograve;n tÄƒng cÆ°á»ng sá»©c máº¡nh cho cÆ¡ ngá»±c.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Ngá»“i tr&ecirc;n 1 cáº¡nh gháº¿</li>\r\n<li>Äáº·t hai tay l&ecirc;n hai cáº¡nh gh&ecirc;, c&aacute;c ng&oacute;n tay duá»—i ra.</li>\r\n<li>Nháº¥c th&acirc;n ngÆ°á»i l&ecirc;n v&agrave; cong gá»‘i 1 g&oacute;c 90 Ä‘á»™ trÆ°á»›c gháº¿.</li>\r\n<li>Tá»« tá»« háº¡ tháº¥p ngÆ°á»i xuá»‘ng d&ugrave;ng sá»©c cá»§a hai tay.</li>\r\n<li>Láº·p láº¡i c&agrave;ng nhiá»u láº§n c&agrave;ng tá»‘t.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Äá»™ng t&aacute;c&nbsp;táº¡ bay</strong></h3>\r\n<p><img src="http://blogthehinh.net/app/webroot/uploads/images/10/2017/12/11/510/bi-quyet-co-bo-nguc-cang-tron-quyen-ru-khong-can-phau-thuat(2).jpg" alt="B&iacute; quyáº¿t c&oacute; bá»™ ngá»±c cÄƒng tr&ograve;n quyáº¿n rÅ© kh&ocirc;ng cáº§n pháº«u thuáº­t" /></p>\r\n<p>Äá»™ng t&aacute;c n&agrave;y d&ugrave;ng sá»©c á»³ xuá»‘ng Ä‘á»ƒ t&aacute;c Ä‘á»™ng l&ecirc;n c&aacute;c cÆ¡ ngá»±c. Káº¿t há»£p táº¡ tay gi&uacute;p báº¡n biáº¿n Ä‘á»•i b&agrave;i táº­p cho ph&ugrave; há»£p vá»›i nhu cáº§u cá»¥ thá»ƒ.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Náº±m ngá»­a lÆ°ng tr&ecirc;n s&agrave;n.</li>\r\n<li>Cong hai gá»‘i v&agrave; Ä‘áº·t l&ograve;ng b&agrave;n ch&acirc;n tr&ecirc;n s&agrave;n</li>\r\n<li>Duá»—i hai c&aacute;nh tay tháº³ng sang hai b&ecirc;n.</li>\r\n<li>Hai tay náº¯m hai táº¡ tay, l&ograve;ng b&agrave;n tay hÆ°á»›ng l&ecirc;n.</li>\r\n<li>K&eacute;o hai táº¡ v&agrave;o nhau theo chuyá»ƒn Ä‘á»™ng c&oacute; kiá»ƒm so&aacute;t, qua sau Ä‘áº§u, sau Ä‘&oacute; quay trá»Ÿ láº¡i vá»‹ tr&iacute; ban Ä‘áº§u v&agrave; láº·p láº¡i.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Äá»™ng t&aacute;c h&iacute;t Ä‘áº¥t b&oacute;ng Medicine Ball</strong></h3>\r\n<p><img src="http://blogthehinh.net/app/webroot/uploads/images/10/2017/12/11/510/bi-quyet-co-bo-nguc-cang-tron-quyen-ru-khong-can-phau-thuat(1).jpg" alt="B&iacute; quyáº¿t c&oacute; bá»™ ngá»±c cÄƒng tr&ograve;n quyáº¿n rÅ© kh&ocirc;ng cáº§n pháº«u thuáº­t" /></p>\r\n<p>H&iacute;t Ä‘áº¥t l&agrave; má»™t b&agrave;i táº­p cho&nbsp; v&ograve;ng má»™t cÄƒng tr&ograve;n Ä‘Æ¡n giáº£n nháº¥t m&agrave; c&oacute; thá»ƒ luyá»‡n táº­p á»Ÿ báº¥t ká»³ Ä‘&acirc;u ná»¯a.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Báº¯t Ä‘áº§u báº±ng tÆ° tháº¿ h&iacute;t Ä‘áº¥t.</li>\r\n<li>Äáº·t má»™t b&oacute;ng dÆ°á»›i l&ograve;ng b&agrave;n tay pháº£i.</li>\r\n<li>CÄƒng cá»©ng cÆ¡ bá»¥ng.</li>\r\n<li>Tá»« tá»« háº¡ tháº¥p th&acirc;n ngÆ°á»i xuá»‘ng Ä‘á»ƒ ho&agrave;n th&agrave;nh Ä‘á»™ng t&aacute;c h&iacute;t Ä‘áº¥t, sau Ä‘&oacute; Ä‘á»•i b&oacute;ng sang tay tr&aacute;i.</li>\r\n<li>Láº·p láº¡i 3-4 v&aacute;n, 10 láº§n láº·p.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Äá»™ng t&aacute;c&nbsp;Ä‘áº©y b&oacute;ng Medicine Ball</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Khi Ä‘áº©y hai tay tháº³ng l&ecirc;n tá»« ngá»±c, báº¡n Ä‘&atilde; t&aacute;c Ä‘á»™ng v&agrave;o c&aacute;c cÆ¡ ngá»±c vá»›i cÆ°á»ng Ä‘á»™ cá»±c ká»³ lá»›n.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>C&aacute;ch n&agrave;y gi&uacute;p Ä‘á»‘t ch&aacute;y c&aacute;c m&ocirc; má»¡ v&agrave; tÄƒng sá»©c máº¡nh.</li>\r\n<li>Náº±m ngá»­a lÆ°ng tr&ecirc;n s&agrave;n, cong hai gá»‘i, l&ograve;ng b&agrave;n ch&acirc;n tr&ecirc;n s&agrave;n.</li>\r\n<li>Hai l&ograve;ng b&agrave;n tay giá»¯ 1 b&oacute;ng Medicine Ball (nhÆ° b&oacute;ng rá»•)</li>\r\n<li>Äáº©y máº¡nh b&oacute;ng tá»« ngá»±c l&ecirc;n cao.</li>\r\n<li>Sau Ä‘&oacute; chá»¥p láº¡i, hai tay duá»—i tháº³ng hÆ¡i cong cong.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Äá»™ng t&aacute;c táº­p&nbsp;Burpees</strong></h3>\r\n<p><img src="http://blogthehinh.net/app/webroot/uploads/images/10/2017/12/11/510/bi-quyet-co-bo-nguc-cang-tron-quyen-ru-khong-can-phau-thuat.jpg" alt="B&iacute; quyáº¿t c&oacute; bá»™ ngá»±c cÄƒng tr&ograve;n quyáº¿n rÅ© kh&ocirc;ng cáº§n pháº«u thuáº­t" /></p>\r\n<p>B&agrave;i&nbsp; táº­p n&agrave;y gi&uacute;p báº¡n l&agrave;m n&oacute;ng ngÆ°á»i báº±ng c&aacute;ch t&aacute;c Ä‘á»™ng v&agrave;o c&aacute;c cÆ¡ ngá»±c. Burpees gi&uacute;p to&agrave;n bá»™ cÆ¡ thá»ƒ báº¡n n&oacute;ng dáº§n l&ecirc;n, v&igrave; váº­y h&atilde;y báº¯t Ä‘áº§u ngay Ä‘áº§u buá»•i táº­p Ä‘á»ƒ gi&uacute;p bÆ¡m m&aacute;u Ä‘i kháº¯p nÆ¡i v&agrave; c&aacute;c cÆ¡ ngá»±c hoáº¡t Ä‘á»™ng nhiá»u hÆ¡n.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Báº¯t Ä‘áº§u báº±ng tÆ° tháº¿ h&iacute;t Ä‘áº¥t.</li>\r\n<li>Nháº£y hai gá»‘i vá» ph&iacute;a ngá»±c, hai tay Ä‘áº·t hai b&ecirc;n tr&ecirc;n s&agrave;n.</li>\r\n<li>Nháº£y l&ecirc;n v&agrave; k&eacute;o hai c&aacute;nh tay l&ecirc;n cao.</li>\r\n<li>Láº·p láº¡i Ä‘á»™ng t&aacute;c k&eacute;o gá»‘i vá» ph&iacute;a ngá»±c, sau Ä‘&oacute; nháº£y rá»“i quay trá»Ÿ láº¡i tÆ° tháº¿ h&iacute;t Ä‘áº¥t.</li>\r\n<li>Láº·p láº¡i 4 v&aacute;n, 20 láº§n láº·p.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Ch&uacute;c chá»‹ em sá»›m c&oacute; Ä‘Æ°á»£c bá»™ ngá»±c cÄƒng tr&ograve;n quyáº¿n rÅ©!</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="clearfix">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p>Nguá»“n: http://www.thehinh.com/2015/12/bai-tap-nguc-cang-tron-hieu-qua.html</p>', '2019-01-18 23:56:54', 'Tips'),
	(7, 'Understanding gym nutrition - Wiggle', 'táº£i xuá»‘ng.jpg', 'understanding-gym-nutrition-wiggle', '<p><strong>As the relatively old saying goes, &lsquo;abs are made in the kitchen, not the gym&rsquo;. The benefits of nutrition before, during, and after your workout...</strong></p>', '<div class="field field--name-field-hero-image field--type-image field--label-hidden">\r\n<div class="field__items">\r\n<div class="field__item even"><img title="Wiggle\'s complete gym nutrition guide" src="https://guides.wiggle.co.uk/sites/default/files/styles/770x480crop/public/hero/sj_wiggle_gym_olympicweight_0014.jpg?itok=u3uxBGXB" alt="Wiggle\'s complete gym nutrition guide" width="800" height="499" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden">\r\n<div class="field__items">\r\n<div class="field__item even">\r\n<p><strong>As the relatively old saying goes, &lsquo;abs are made in the kitchen, not the gym&rsquo;. The benefits of nutrition before, during, and after your workout are well accepted but not well understood.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Of course, you still need to work out, but nutrition remains a pivotal area for gym goers. It&rsquo;s a complex area, with no single solution or approach that works&nbsp;equally well for everyone. But it\'s often a lack of understanding of the basic tenants of sports nutrition which leads many to overlook this important area.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>There are many types of nutritional supplements, all with different purposes, taken at different times, and with altering levels of effectiveness.</p>\r\n<p>That makes it a good idea to try a range of food and supplement variations to find out what works for you and provides results.</p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s a good idea to keep a diary of what you eat, including your nutritional supplements, and track these against your performance gains. That way, you can know for sure if your food regime &ndash; for it should be a &lsquo;regime&rsquo; &ndash; is as effective as your lifting techniques and work out schedule.</p>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ll also find out if what you&rsquo;re taking and the diet you&rsquo;re following is simply hype or the real thing &ndash; data is key!</p>\r\n<h2>It\'s not just about protein</h2>\r\n<p>You will&nbsp;have undoubtedly heard about the need for protein in your diet, but that is just the tip of the sports nutrition iceberg.</p>\r\n<p>There is a world of nutritional advantage, used by professional athletes, personal trainers, and dedicated amateurs everywhere, aimed at making every moment in the gym count.</p>\r\n<p>The breadth and depth of the options out there can be confusing, so in this guide we&rsquo;ll take a look at some of the main nutritional supplements, how they work and what they&rsquo;re for, so you can decide if they&rsquo;re right for you.</p>\r\n<p>So whether you want a better understanding of&nbsp;gym nutrition for beginners, or have questions about supplements you&rsquo;ve heard about from others, this guide should explain all.</p>\r\n<p>Remember, nutritional supplements should be taken only as part of an otherwise balanced and healthy diet, not as meal replacements.</p>\r\n<p><img src="https://guides.wiggle.co.uk/sites/default/files/resize/guides/gym-guide-1024x1024-cross-768x768.jpg" alt="" width="768" height="768" /></p>\r\n<h2>Protein</h2>\r\n<p><strong>What is it?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Protein is a macro-nutrient, essential for building muscle mass. It&rsquo;s one of the three macro-nutrients, the others being fats and carbohydrates. It is composed of amino acids &ndash; a fundamental building block of human tissue &ndash; and is found in abundance in animal products, nuts, and legumes. For gym goers, it&rsquo;s commonly found in the form of whey protein powder, which contains a wide range of amino acids that are absorbed quickly. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>What does it do?</strong></p>\r\n<p>By lifting weights, we put strain on our muscles. This strain creates micro-tears in the muscle tissue, a natural process that stimulates repair, creating&nbsp;stronger, bigger, and denser muscles that&nbsp;allow&nbsp;you to lift more next time. However, to make these repairs, and for muscle maintenance, the body needs protein. The more tears you make, the more protein you need. But remember, the body can only handle so much!</p>\r\n<p><strong>How is it consumed?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Many gym goers and athletes consume additional quantities of protein in powder form, mixed with liquid,&nbsp;due to its convenience and ease of digestion. It can also be found in gym kit-friendly bars and drinks. Solid food takes longer to digest and break down protein in plants or animal products before sending it to the muscles.</p>\r\n<p><strong>When should I take protein?</strong></p>\r\n<p>There is a general consensus that taking protein within the &lsquo;magic hour&rsquo; (or even half-hour), after your training session is vitally important to muscle growth and repair, although the length of this important period has been&nbsp;challenged somewhat. Protein should be part of a balanced diet and consumed throughout the day, including two to three hours before your work out. Many gym goers consume between 20g to 30g in a single day, although this varies in accordance with your body weight and goals. There is a limit to how much protein the human body can digest in a day.</p>\r\n<p>Here are&nbsp;a few examples of protein supplements from Wiggle...</p>\r\n<p><span class="tooltip-wrapper"><a class="external tooltip" href="http://www.wiggle.co.uk/puori-pw1-organic-whey-protein?utm_source=guides.wiggle.co.uk&amp;utm_medium=wiggle-content&amp;utm_campaign=nutrition&amp;utm_content=understanding-gym-nutrition-wiggles-complete-guide&amp;utm_term=Product" rel="nofollow" data-ptitle="Puori PW1 Organic Whey Protein" data-pdid="100479306">Puori PW1 Organic Whey Protein</a></span></p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.wiggle.co.uk/puori-pw1-organic-whey-protein/?utm_source=content&amp;utm_medium=guides&amp;utm_campaign=gymnutritionbuyingguide2018" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://guides.wiggle.co.uk/sites/default/files/resize/guides/puori-wheypoeder-vanille-pure-pharma-400x400.jpg" alt="Puori PW1 Organic Whey Protein" width="400" height="400" /></a></p>\r\n<p><span class="tooltip-wrapper"><a class="external tooltip" href="http://www.wiggle.co.uk/high5-recovery-drink-16kg-1?utm_source=guides.wiggle.co.uk&amp;utm_medium=wiggle-content&amp;utm_campaign=nutrition&amp;utm_content=understanding-gym-nutrition-wiggles-complete-guide&amp;utm_term=Product" rel="nofollow" data-ptitle="High5 Recovery Drink (1.6kg)" data-pdid="5360025039">High5 Recovery Drink (1.6kg)</a></span></p>\r\n<p><img src="https://guides.wiggle.co.uk/sites/default/files/u1876/high5-recovery-drink-1-6kg-energy-recovery-drink-banana-100989160066gbr.jpg" alt="" width="430" height="430" /></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><a class="cta" href="https://www.wiggle.co.uk/nutrition/?s=protein/&amp;utm_source=content&amp;utm_medium=guides&amp;utm_campaign=gymnutritionbuyingguide2018" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Shop Protein supplements at Wiggle</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div><hr />\r\n<h2>Carbohydrate</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><strong>What is it?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Carbohydrate&nbsp;has&nbsp;become somewhat of a dirty word in fitness circles, but its value has been widely misunderstood. It\'s&nbsp;found in the sugars, starches, and fibres of fruits, grains, vegetables and milk products.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What does it do?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Firstly, carbohydrates are a major fuel source for your body, allowing you to work out harder and for longer. Secondly, it&rsquo;s important for stopping your body from converting your muscles back into energy when it starts to run out of fuel.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How is it consumed?</strong></p>\r\n<p>There are a variety of gels, drinks, bars, and powders available that can deliver a big boost for the energy in your bloodstream when required. It&rsquo;s often combined with &lsquo;electrolytes&rsquo; which helps muscles push harder and perform better.</p>\r\n<p><strong>When should I take carbohydrates?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Carbohydrates should be consumed throughout the day, especially before a training session to provide fuel for the body. Most carbohydrate needs can be met by eating a healthy balanced diet that includes plenty of fruits and vegetables. However, if caught short, you should consume some carbs &ndash; such as a quickly absorbing gel or drink, between 30 and 60 minutes before beginning. These &lsquo;fast carb&rsquo; supplements can also be taken after an intense workout to stop your body from turning spare protein into fuel.</p>\r\n<p>Here are&nbsp;some examples from Wiggle...</p>\r\n<p><span class="tooltip-wrapper"><a class="external tooltip" href="http://www.wiggle.co.uk/high5-energy-drink-22kg?utm_source=guides.wiggle.co.uk&amp;utm_medium=wiggle-content&amp;utm_campaign=nutrition&amp;utm_content=understanding-gym-nutrition-wiggles-complete-guide&amp;utm_term=Product" rel="nofollow" data-ptitle="High5 Energy Drink 2.2kg" data-pdid="5360025287">High5 Energy Drink 2.2kg</a></span></p>\r\n<p><img src="https://guides.wiggle.co.uk/sites/default/files/u1876/high5-energy-source-2-2kg-tub-energy-recovery-drink-orange-100988220011gbr.jpg" alt="" width="430" height="430" /></p>\r\n<p><span class="tooltip-wrapper"><a class="external tooltip" href="http://www.wiggle.co.uk/science-in-sport-go-isotonic-gels-30-x-60ml-1?utm_source=guides.wiggle.co.uk&amp;utm_medium=wiggle-content&amp;utm_campaign=nutrition&amp;utm_content=understanding-gym-nutrition-wiggles-complete-guide&amp;utm_term=Product" rel="nofollow" data-ptitle="Science in Sport GO Isotonic Gels (30 x 60ml)" data-pdid="5360010677">Science in Sport GO Isotonic Gels (30 x 60ml)</a></span></p>\r\n<p><img src="https://guides.wiggle.co.uk/sites/default/files/u1876/science-in-sport-go-isotonic-gels-30-x-60ml-41-60g-chocolate-21-3-gels-blackcurrant-002955.jpg" alt="" width="430" height="430" /></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><a class="cta" href="https://www.wiggle.co.uk/?s=carbohydrates/&amp;utm_source=content&amp;utm_medium=guides&amp;utm_campaign=gymnutritionbuyingguide2018" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Shop Carbohydrate supplements at Wiggle</a></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2>Creatine</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><strong>What is it?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Creatine is a nitrogen-rich organic acid that occurs naturally in humans. It can also be found in small quantities in meat and fish.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What does it do?</strong></p>\r\n<p>It is involved in supplying muscles with the energy they need to contract, allowing you to train harder, and more often, producing faster results. There have been some anecdotal side-effects, but its effects are proven and can be significant. However, restraint and care should be taken, and it&rsquo;s recommended for consumption by experienced adult gym-goers only.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How is it consumed?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Creatine is most commonly consumed in powder form but is also available as a capsule. It&rsquo;s mostly consumed in quantities of around 2-5 grams per day by those working out at intense levels almost every day.</p>\r\n<p><strong>When should I take creatine?</strong></p>\r\n<p>The best time of day to take a creatine supplement is around 30 minutes to 1 hour before your training session and immediately post-workout alongside or as part of a protein shake.</p>\r\n<p><span class="tooltip-wrapper"><a class="external tooltip" href="http://www.wiggle.co.uk/science-in-sport-creatine-400g?utm_source=guides.wiggle.co.uk&amp;utm_medium=wiggle-content&amp;utm_campaign=nutrition&amp;utm_content=understanding-gym-nutrition-wiggles-complete-guide&amp;utm_term=Product" rel="nofollow" data-ptitle="Science in Sport Creatine (400g)" data-pdid="100508054">Science in Sport Creatine (400g)</a></span></p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.wiggle.co.uk/science-in-sport-creatine-400g/?utm_source=content&amp;utm_medium=guides&amp;utm_campaign=gymnutritionbuyingguide2018" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://guides.wiggle.co.uk/sites/default/files/resize/guides/sis_creatine-400x342.jpg" alt="Science in Sport Creatine (400g)" width="400" height="342" /></a></p>\r\n<p><span class="tooltip-wrapper"><a class="external tooltip" href="http://www.wiggle.co.uk/bio-synergy-creatine-plus-strength-125-capsules?utm_source=guides.wiggle.co.uk&amp;utm_medium=wiggle-content&amp;utm_campaign=nutrition&amp;utm_content=understanding-gym-nutrition-wiggles-complete-guide&amp;utm_term=Product" rel="nofollow" data-ptitle="Bio-Synergy Creatine Plus Strength (125 capsules)" data-pdid="5360111410">Bio-Synergy Creatine Plus Strength (125 capsules)</a></span></p>\r\n<p><img src="https://guides.wiggle.co.uk/sites/default/files/u1876/creatine-plus-phase-strength.jpg" alt="" width="430" height="430" /></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><a class="cta" href="https://www.wiggle.co.uk/?s=creatine/&amp;utm_source=content&amp;utm_medium=guides&amp;utm_campaign=gymnutritionbuyingguide2018" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Shop Creatine supplements at Wiggle</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><img src="https://guides.wiggle.co.uk/sites/default/files/resize/blogs/sj_wiggle_gym_130717_olympicweight_0050-768x504.jpg" alt="" width="768" height="504" /><br />Magnesium</h2>\r\n<p><strong>What is it?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Magnesium is a chemical element that is necessary for muscle contractions while training, along with a whole host of other important biological functions. It&rsquo;s found in green leafy vegetables, fruits such as figs and avocados, nuts, seeds, legumes, and seafood. It&rsquo;s taken as a supplement due to its omission from the modern grain-rich diet. Magnesium is also lost through sweat, which is why it&rsquo;s often taken as a supplement by athletes despite their otherwise balanced diets.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What does it do?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Magnesium is crucial to nerve transmission, muscle contraction, blood coagulation, energy production, nutrient metabolism and bone and cell formation. For weight-lifting and gym work, its an invaluable part of the muscle repair process. It also promotes sleep &ndash; a vital time for muscle growth and repair - and it helps improve recovery.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How is it consumed?</strong></p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s mostly found in capsule form, or as a liquid. It can also be combined with fish oil supplements and soluble drink tablets.</p>\r\n<p><strong>When should I take magnesium?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Magnesium supplements are commonly taken before bed, but care should be taken on whether or not you are able to take it on an empty stomach.</p>\r\n<p>Here are some examples from Wiggle...</p>\r\n<p><span class="tooltip-wrapper"><a class="external tooltip" href="http://www.wiggle.co.uk/puori-m3-magnesium-120-capsules?utm_source=guides.wiggle.co.uk&amp;utm_medium=wiggle-content&amp;utm_campaign=nutrition&amp;utm_content=understanding-gym-nutrition-wiggles-complete-guide&amp;utm_term=Product" rel="nofollow" data-ptitle="Puori M3 - Magnesium (120 capsules)" data-pdid="100479292">Puori M3 - Magnesium (120 capsules)</a></span></p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.wiggle.co.uk/puori-m3-magnesium-120-capsules/?utm_source=content&amp;utm_medium=guides&amp;utm_campaign=gymnutritionbuyingguide2018" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://guides.wiggle.co.uk/sites/default/files/resize/guides/puori-m3-magnesium-400x400.jpg" alt="Puori M3 - Magnesium (120 capsules)" width="400" height="400" /></a></p>\r\n<p><span class="tooltip-wrapper"><a class="external tooltip" href="http://www.wiggle.co.uk/powerbar-magnesium-ampoules-box-of-20-tubes?utm_source=guides.wiggle.co.uk&amp;utm_medium=wiggle-content&amp;utm_campaign=nutrition&amp;utm_content=understanding-gym-nutrition-wiggles-complete-guide&amp;utm_term=Product" rel="nofollow" data-ptitle="PowerBar Magnesium Ampoules box of 20 tubes" data-pdid="5360091260">PowerBar Magnesium Ampoules box of 20 tubes</a></span></p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.wiggle.co.uk/powerbar-magnesium-ampoules-box-of-20-tubes/?utm_source=content&amp;utm_medium=guides&amp;utm_campaign=gymnutritionbuyingguide2018" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://guides.wiggle.co.uk/sites/default/files/resize/guides/powerbar_magnesium-400x400.jpg" alt="PowerBar Magnesium Ampoules box of 20 tubes" width="400" height="400" /></a></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><a class="cta" href="https://www.wiggle.co.uk/nutrition/?s=magnesium&amp;utm_source=content&amp;utm_medium=guides&amp;utm_campaign=gymnutritionbuyingguide2018/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Shop Magnesium supplements at Wiggle</a></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2>Branched-Chain Amino Acids (BCAAs)</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><strong>What are they?</strong></p>\r\n<p>There are three BCAAs: leucine, isoleucine and valine. These are amino-acids that make up around one third of muscle protein. They are especially important as the body is unable to make them out of other amino acids, meaning they must be ingested through food or supplements. They can be found in varying levels within protein rich foods, such as eggs, meat, nuts or legumes.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What do they do?</strong></p>\r\n<p>While present in many protein-rich foods, BCAAs can benefit the body significantly if taken at specific times. They reduce catabolism - the action of muscles breaking down &ndash; and stimulate muscle growth.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How is it consumed?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Supplementary BCAAs are mostly consumed in powder or capsule form, and generally combined with other supplements in energy drinks.</p>\r\n<p><strong>When should I take BCAAs?</strong></p>\r\n<p>BCAAs are commonly consumed before, after, and sometimes during workouts. Typically, 5-10 grams is added to a pre- and post-workout shake. For those aiming to build mass, a dose of BCAAs are&nbsp;also taken upon waking in the morning to stop the muscle breakdown triggered during the night when the body hasn&rsquo;t consumed food for the duration of your sleep.</p>\r\n<p>Again, a few examples from Wiggle\'s range...</p>\r\n<p><span class="tooltip-wrapper"><a class="external tooltip" href="http://www.wiggle.co.uk/dymatize-bcaas-300g?utm_source=guides.wiggle.co.uk&amp;utm_medium=wiggle-content&amp;utm_campaign=nutrition&amp;utm_content=understanding-gym-nutrition-wiggles-complete-guide&amp;utm_term=Product" rel="nofollow" data-ptitle="Dymatize BCAA\'s (300g)" data-pdid="100394550">Dymatize BCAA\'s (300g)</a></span></p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.wiggle.co.uk/dymatize-bcaas-300g/?utm_source=content&amp;utm_medium=guides&amp;utm_campaign=gymnutritionbuyingguide2018" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://guides.wiggle.co.uk/sites/default/files/resize/guides/dymatize-bcaa-300g-ireland-400x400.png" alt="" width="400" height="400" /></a></p>\r\n<p><span class="tooltip-wrapper"><a class="external tooltip" href="http://www.wiggle.co.uk/reflex-bcaa-intra-fusion-400g?utm_source=guides.wiggle.co.uk&amp;utm_medium=wiggle-content&amp;utm_campaign=nutrition&amp;utm_content=understanding-gym-nutrition-wiggles-complete-guide&amp;utm_term=Product" rel="nofollow" data-ptitle="Reflex BCAA Intra Fusion (400g)" data-pdid="100504874">Reflex BCAA Intra Fusion (400g)</a></span></p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.wiggle.co.uk/reflex-bcaa-intra-fusion-400g/?utm_source=content&amp;utm_medium=guides&amp;utm_campaign=gymnutritionbuyingguide2018" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://guides.wiggle.co.uk/sites/default/files/resize/guides/bcaa-intra-fusion-400g-400x400.jpg" alt="Reflex BCAA Intra Fusion (400g)" width="400" height="400" /></a></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><a class="cta" href="https://www.wiggle.co.uk/?s=BCAA/&amp;utm_source=content&amp;utm_medium=guides&amp;utm_campaign=gymnutritionbuyingguide2018" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Shop BCAAs supplements at Wiggle</a></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2>Caffeine</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><strong>What is it?</strong></p>\r\n<p>We&rsquo;re sure you&rsquo;re familiar with caffeine, especially in its most common form &ndash; coffee. It&rsquo;s a central nervous system (CNS) stimulant, and technically the world&rsquo;s most widely consumed psychoactive drug.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What does it do?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Caffeine is increasingly becoming important as a nutritional supplement in the gym. It has been shown to stimulate the body into using&nbsp;fat cells for energy instead of other fuel sources &ndash; such as your muscle mass. It also raises your metabolism, which makes you burn more calories throughout the day, boosts pain tolerance, and helps you workout for longer periods.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How is it consumed?</strong></p>\r\n<p>In terms of workout supplements, caffeine can be found in capsules, gels, concentrated drinks and even bars. Of course, drinking a cup of coffee has much the same effect, but not everyone likes the taste of coffee, while others are not always able to make a cup on their journey&nbsp;to the gym. It is also found as an ingredient in sports drinks, powders, and foods.</p>\r\n<p><strong>When should I take it?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Caffeine is absorbed from the stomach within 15 to 45 minutes of consumption, while its peak stimulatory effects kick in between 30 and 75 minutes after your dose. So taking on caffeine around an hour before your workout is optimal.</p>\r\n<p>And a few examples from the Wiggle site...</p>\r\n<p><span class="tooltip-wrapper"><a class="external tooltip" href="http://www.wiggle.co.uk/high5-zero-caffeine-hit-8x20-tabs-1?utm_source=guides.wiggle.co.uk&amp;utm_medium=wiggle-content&amp;utm_campaign=nutrition&amp;utm_content=understanding-gym-nutrition-wiggles-complete-guide&amp;utm_term=Product" rel="nofollow" data-ptitle="High5 ZERO Caffeine Hit (8x20 tabs)" data-pdid="82100">High5 ZERO Caffeine Hit (8x20 tabs)</a></span></p>\r\n<p><img src="https://guides.wiggle.co.uk/sites/default/files/u1876/high5-zero-caffeine-hit-8x20-tabs-energy-recovery-drink-grapefruit-notset-106995016061gbr.jpg" alt="" width="430" height="430" /></p>\r\n<p><span class="tooltip-wrapper"><a class="external tooltip" href="http://www.wiggle.co.uk/science-in-sport-go-energy-gel-caffeine-6-x-60ml?utm_source=guides.wiggle.co.uk&amp;utm_medium=wiggle-content&amp;utm_campaign=nutrition&amp;utm_content=understanding-gym-nutrition-wiggles-complete-guide&amp;utm_term=Product" rel="nofollow" data-ptitle="Science in Sport GO Energy Gel+ Caffeine 6 x 60ml" data-pdid="5360103910">Science in Sport GO Energy Gel+ Caffeine 6 x 60ml</a></span></p>\r\n<p><img src="https://guides.wiggle.co.uk/sites/default/files/u1876/cola_caf.jpg" alt="" width="430" height="430" /></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><a class="cta" href="https://www.wiggle.co.uk/?s=caffeine/&amp;utm_source=content&amp;utm_medium=guides&amp;utm_campaign=gymnutritionbuyingguide2018" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Shop Caffeine supplements at Wiggle</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '2019-02-02 21:53:40', 'nutrition'),
	(8, 'CÃ¡ch hÃ­t xÃ  Ä‘Æ¡n Ä‘á»ƒ cÆ¡ vai cÆ¡ tay sÄƒn cháº¯c', 'lam-sao-co-vai-va-bap-tay-san-chac-neu-1.png', 'cach-hit-xa-don-de-co-vai-co-tay-san-chac', '<p>H&iacute;t x&agrave; Ä‘Æ¡n l&agrave; b&agrave;i táº­p gi&uacute;p cÆ¡ vai v&agrave; cÆ¡ tay cá»§a báº¡n sÄƒn cháº¯c nháº¥t, tuy nhi&ecirc;n náº¿u báº¡n táº­p sai Ä‘á»™ng t&aacute;c h&iacute;t..</p>', '<div class="post-single-content box mark-links entry-content">\r\n<div class="thecontent">\r\n<h2>H&iacute;t x&agrave; Ä‘Æ¡n l&agrave; b&agrave;i táº­p gi&uacute;p cÆ¡ vai v&agrave; cÆ¡ tay cá»§a báº¡n sÄƒn cháº¯c nháº¥t, tuy nhi&ecirc;n náº¿u báº¡n táº­p sai Ä‘á»™ng t&aacute;c h&iacute;t x&agrave; th&igrave; sáº½ kh&ocirc;ng hiá»‡u quáº£ nhÆ° tháº¿ Ä‘&acirc;u.</h2>\r\n<h3><strong>D&ugrave;ng ch&acirc;n Ä‘á»ƒ táº¡o lá»±c Ä‘áº©y ngÆ°á»i l&ecirc;n khi h&iacute;t x&agrave;</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Ä&acirc;y ch&iacute;nh l&agrave; sai láº§m m&agrave; háº§u háº¿t gymer máº¯c pháº£i , bá»Ÿi khi ngÆ°á»i d&ugrave;ng n&oacute; Ä‘á»ƒ báº¯t Ä‘áº§u b&agrave;i táº­p Ä‘Æ°a cÆ¡ thá»ƒ l&ecirc;n ph&iacute;a tr&ecirc;n x&agrave;. Khi báº¡n báº¯t Ä‘áº§u h&iacute;t x&agrave; Ä‘Æ¡n, báº¡n cáº§n phá»‘i há»£p sá»©c máº¡nh cá»§a lÆ°ng tr&ecirc;n, cÆ¡ x&ocirc;, c&aacute;nh tay, cá»‘t l&otilde;i v&agrave; kháº£ nÄƒng b&aacute;m cháº¯c. T&igrave;nh tráº¡ng cÆ¡ x&ocirc; yáº¿u l&agrave; má»™t nhÆ°á»£c Ä‘iá»ƒm lá»›n Ä‘á»‘i vá»›i nhiá»u ngÆ°á»i, dáº«n Ä‘áº¿n xu hÆ°á»›ng &ldquo;Äƒn gian&rdquo; má»™t c&aacute;ch tráº¯ng trá»£n báº±ng c&aacute;ch giáº­t máº¡nh ch&acirc;n Ä‘á»ƒ táº¡o lá»±c Ä‘áº©y th&acirc;n ngÆ°á»i l&ecirc;n dá»… d&agrave;ng hÆ¡n.</p>\r\n<p><img title="" src="http://blogthehinh.net/uploads/images/10/2017/12/11/491/lam-sao-co-vai-va-bap-tay-san-chac-neu-2.png" alt="L&agrave;m sao cÆ¡ vai v&agrave; báº¯p tay sÄƒn cháº¯c náº¿u máº¯c lá»—i khi h&iacute;t x&agrave; Ä‘Æ¡n?" /></p>\r\n<p>Äiá»u n&agrave;y thoáº¡t nh&igrave;n tÆ°Æ¡ng tá»± nhÆ° báº¡n Ä‘ang táº­p Ä‘á»™ng t&aacute;c h&iacute;t x&agrave; thá»±c thá»¥, nhÆ°ng thá»±c táº¿ Ä‘iá»u Ä‘&oacute; khiáº¿n báº¡n Ä‘ang l&atilde;ng ph&iacute; thá»i gian v&agrave; cÆ¡ há»™i ph&aacute;t triá»ƒn sá»©c máº¡nh to&agrave;n diá»‡n cá»§a cÆ¡ thá»ƒ v&agrave; c&aacute;c nh&oacute;m cÆ¡ vai v&agrave; báº¯p tay. V&igrave; váº­y, náº¿u ch&acirc;n báº¡n Ä‘ung Ä‘Æ°a, báº¡n cáº§n pháº£i dá»“n lá»±c l&ecirc;n khu vá»±c cá»‘t l&otilde;i (core).</p>\r\n<h3>Sai vá»‹ tr&iacute; khuá»·u tay</h3>\r\n<p>Trong Ä‘á»™ng t&aacute;c h&iacute;t x&agrave; Ä‘Æ¡n (lÆ°u &yacute; l&agrave; kh&aacute;c vá»›i h&iacute;t x&agrave; Ä‘Æ¡n ngá»­a tay &ndash; chin up), khi báº¡n k&eacute;o ngÆ°á»i l&ecirc;n, th&igrave; khuá»·u tay cáº§n Ä‘Æ°á»£c Ä‘áº©y xuá»‘ng v&agrave; hÆ°á»›ng vá» sau nhÆ° thá»ƒ l&agrave; báº¡n Ä‘ang cá»‘ gáº¯ng Ä‘á»ƒ &ldquo;Ä‘áº·t khuá»·u tay v&agrave;o t&uacute;i sau&rdquo;.</p>\r\n<p><img title="" src="http://blogthehinh.net/uploads/images/10/2017/12/11/491/lam-sao-co-vai-va-bap-tay-san-chac-neu-3.png" alt="L&agrave;m sao cÆ¡ vai v&agrave; báº¯p tay sÄƒn cháº¯c náº¿u máº¯c lá»—i khi h&iacute;t x&agrave; Ä‘Æ¡n?" /></p>\r\n<p>Sai vá»‹ tr&iacute; khuá»·u tayKhi báº¡n h&iacute;t l&ecirc;n, hai khuá»·u tay qu&aacute; gáº§n nhau hoáº·c khuá»·u tay á»Ÿ ngay ph&iacute;a trÆ°á»›c ngá»±c sáº½ khiáº¿n báº¡n pháº£i sá»­ dá»¥ng cÆ¡ tay trÆ°á»›c nhiá»u hÆ¡n (Ä‘iá»u n&agrave;y c&oacute; thá»ƒ l&agrave; á»•n náº¿u báº¡n c&oacute; dá»± Ä‘á»‹nh nhÆ° váº­y).</p>\r\n<p><img title="" src="http://blogthehinh.net/uploads/images/10/2017/12/11/491/lam-sao-co-vai-va-bap-tay-san-chac-neu-4.png" alt="L&agrave;m sao cÆ¡ vai v&agrave; báº¯p tay sÄƒn cháº¯c náº¿u máº¯c lá»—i khi h&iacute;t x&agrave; Ä‘Æ¡n?" /></p>\r\n<h3>Qu&aacute; n&oacute;ng vá»™i khi má»›i báº¯t Ä‘áº§u</h3>\r\n<p>Hiá»‡n tÆ°á»£ng n&agrave;y thÆ°á»ng xuáº¥t hiá»‡n má»™t c&aacute;ch phá»• biáº¿n á»Ÿ háº§u háº¿t á»Ÿ táº¥t cáº£ c&aacute;c b&agrave;i táº­p. Th&oacute;i quen n&oacute;ng vá»™i thÆ°á»ng xuáº¥t hiá»‡n Ä‘a sá»‘ á»Ÿ nhá»¯ng ngÆ°á»i má»›i táº­p luyá»‡n, hay nháº£y c&oacute;c c&aacute;c b&agrave;i táº­p v&agrave; muá»‘n táº­p tháº­t nhiá»u Ä‘á»ƒ c&oacute; thá»ƒ gi&uacute;p cho&nbsp;<strong>cÆ¡ vai v&agrave; báº¯p tay sÄƒn cháº¯c</strong>&nbsp;nhanh hÆ¡n. Ä&oacute; l&agrave; quan niá»‡m ho&agrave;n to&agrave;n sai láº§m Ä‘áº¥y.</p>\r\n<p>Qu&aacute; vá»™i v&agrave;ng khi má»›i báº¯t Ä‘áº§uH&iacute;t x&agrave; Ä‘Æ¡n l&agrave; má»™t b&agrave;i táº­p tuyá»‡t vá»i Ä‘á»ƒ n&acirc;ng cao sá»©c máº¡nh tá»•ng thá»ƒ, nhÆ°ng n&oacute; tháº­t sá»± kh&ocirc;ng há» dá»… d&agrave;ng nhÆ° báº¡n thÆ°á»ng nghÄ©. Náº¿u báº¡n má»›i báº¯t Ä‘áº§u táº­p luyá»‡n, h&atilde;y ki&ecirc;n nháº«n v&agrave; tiáº¿n tá»«ng bÆ°á»›c nhá». TrÆ°á»›c ti&ecirc;n, báº¡n cáº§n r&egrave;n luyá»‡n kháº£ nÄƒng b&aacute;m cháº·t nhá» n&acirc;ng táº¡ Ä‘Æ¡n v&agrave; táº¡ Ä‘&ograve;n, sá»©c máº¡nh cá»§a cÆ¡ x&ocirc; v&agrave; cÆ¡ tay trÆ°á»›c. Náº¿u báº¡n qu&aacute; n&oacute;ng vá»™i m&agrave; dáº«n Ä‘áº¿n táº­p luyá»‡n qu&aacute; sá»©c th&igrave; áº£nh hÆ°á»Ÿng kh&ocirc;ng chá»‰ tá»›i b&agrave;i táº­p kh&ocirc;ng hiá»‡u quáº£ m&agrave; c&ograve;n nhá»¯ng cháº¥n thÆ°Æ¡ng kh&ocirc;ng tá»‘t cho sá»©c khá»e cá»§a báº¡n vá» sau.</p>\r\n<h3>Xoay vai v&agrave;o trong</h3>\r\n<p>Má»™t trong nhá»¯ng má»¥c ti&ecirc;u ch&iacute;nh khi h&iacute;t x&agrave; Ä‘Æ¡n l&agrave; dá»“n lá»±c l&ecirc;n cÆ¡ x&ocirc; c&agrave;ng nhiá»u c&agrave;ng tá»‘t. Khi xoay vai v&agrave;o trong v&agrave; rÆ°á»›n l&ecirc;n theo chuyá»ƒn Ä‘á»™ng cá»§a ná»­a tr&ecirc;n cÆ¡ thá»ƒ, báº¡n c&oacute; biáº¿t l&agrave; táº¥t cáº£ nhá»¯ng g&igrave; báº¡n Ä‘ang l&agrave;m Ä‘áº·t &aacute;p lá»±c l&ecirc;n vai v&agrave; c&aacute;c cÆ¡ kh&ocirc;ng cáº§n thiáº¿t, trong khi Ä‘&oacute; láº¡i giáº£m thiá»ƒu t&aacute;c Ä‘á»™ng l&ecirc;n cÆ¡ x&ocirc;.</p>\r\n<p><img title="" src="http://blogthehinh.net/uploads/images/10/2017/12/11/491/lam-sao-co-vai-va-bap-tay-san-chac-neu-6.png" alt="L&agrave;m sao cÆ¡ vai v&agrave; báº¯p tay sÄƒn cháº¯c náº¿u máº¯c lá»—i khi h&iacute;t x&agrave; Ä‘Æ¡n?" /></p>\r\n<p>Xoay vai v&agrave;o trongÄá»ƒ kháº¯c phá»¥c Ä‘iá»u n&agrave;y, ngay tá»« vá»‹ tr&iacute; báº¯t Ä‘áº§u, báº¡n n&ecirc;n chá»§ Ä‘á»™ng háº¡ vai xuá»‘ng v&agrave; hÆ°á»›ng ra sau (giá»¯ nguy&ecirc;n nhÆ° váº­y trong suá»‘t Ä‘á»™ng t&aacute;c) v&agrave; sau Ä‘&oacute; k&eacute;o ngÆ°á»i l&ecirc;n vá»›i sá»± há»— trá»£ cá»§a ngá»±c. Khi thá»±c hiá»‡n Ä‘á»™ng t&aacute;c nhÆ° váº­y, báº¡n sáº½ nháº­n tháº¥y sá»± cáº£i thiá»‡n lá»±c Ä‘&aacute;ng ká»ƒ l&ecirc;n cÆ¡ x&ocirc; gi&uacute;p cho cÆ¡ vai sÄƒn cháº¯c hÆ¡n.</p>\r\n<h3>Kh&ocirc;ng quan t&acirc;m Ä‘áº¿n nhá»‹p thá»Ÿ</h3>\r\n<p>Nhá»‹p thá»Ÿ Ä‘&oacute;ng vai tr&ograve; ráº¥t quan trá»ng trong qu&aacute; tr&igrave;nh báº¡n táº­p vá»›i x&agrave; Ä‘Æ¡n hay báº¥t k&igrave; b&agrave;i táº­p thá»ƒ h&igrave;nh n&agrave;o. Ráº¥t nhiá»u ngÆ°á»i ngÆ°á»i kh&ocirc;ng kiá»ƒm so&aacute;t Ä‘Æ°á»£c nhá»‹p thá»Ÿ cá»§a m&igrave;nh khi táº­p, dáº«n Ä‘áº¿n nhá»‹p thá»Ÿ kh&ocirc;ng Ä‘á»u v&agrave; khiáº¿n báº¡n ráº¥t nhanh má»‡t.</p>\r\n<p><img title="" src="http://blogthehinh.net/uploads/images/10/2017/12/11/491/lam-sao-co-vai-va-bap-tay-san-chac-neu-7.png" alt="L&agrave;m sao cÆ¡ vai v&agrave; báº¯p tay sÄƒn cháº¯c náº¿u máº¯c lá»—i khi h&iacute;t x&agrave; Ä‘Æ¡n?" /></p>\r\n<p>Kh&ocirc;ng quan t&acirc;m Ä‘áº¿n nhá»‹p thá»ŸKhi l&ecirc;n x&agrave; l&agrave; l&uacute;c lá»“ng ngá»±c gi&atilde;n ra, báº¡n cáº§n h&iacute;t v&agrave;o. Khi xuá»‘ng, tay tháº£ tá»« tá»«, lá»“ng ngá»±c v&agrave; cÆ¡ ho&agrave;nh co láº¡i, báº¡n cáº§n thá»Ÿ ra. B&ecirc;n cáº¡nh Ä‘&oacute;, báº¡n n&ecirc;n giá»¯ nhá»‹p thá»Ÿ s&acirc;u cháº­m v&agrave; Ä‘á»u Ä‘á»ƒ cÆ¡ vai v&agrave; báº¯p tay ph&aacute;t triá»ƒn tá»‘t nháº¥t.</p>\r\n<h3>Kh&ocirc;ng thá»±c hiá»‡n Ä‘áº§y Ä‘á»§ chuyá»ƒn Ä‘á»™ng</h3>\r\n<p>T&igrave;nh tráº¡ng táº­p kh&ocirc;ng Ä‘áº¿n nÆ¡i diá»…n ra ráº¥t phá»• biáº¿n á»Ÿ anh em thá»ƒ h&igrave;nh kh&ocirc;ng chuy&ecirc;n nghiá»‡p. Viá»‡c táº­p luyá»‡n dá»Ÿ dang ho&agrave;n to&agrave;n kh&ocirc;ng mang láº¡i hiá»‡u quáº£ cho qu&aacute; tr&igrave;nh báº¡n táº­p luyá»‡n, n&oacute; khiáº¿n báº¡n máº¥t thá»i gian v&agrave; c&ocirc;ng sá»©c táº­p luyá»‡n v&ocirc; &iacute;ch.</p>\r\n<p><img title="" src="http://blogthehinh.net/uploads/images/10/2017/12/11/491/lam-sao-co-vai-va-bap-tay-san-chac-neu-8.png" alt="L&agrave;m sao cÆ¡ vai v&agrave; báº¯p tay sÄƒn cháº¯c náº¿u máº¯c lá»—i khi h&iacute;t x&agrave; Ä‘Æ¡n?" /></p>\r\n<p>Kh&ocirc;ng thá»±c hiá»‡n Ä‘áº§y Ä‘á»§ chuyá»ƒn Ä‘á»™ngBáº¡n cá»‘ gáº¯ng Ä‘á»«ng thá»±c hiá»‡n Ä‘á»™ng t&aacute;c ná»­a vá»i, nhÆ° háº¡ ngÆ°á»i xuá»‘ng kh&ocirc;ng Ä‘á»§ tháº¥p hay n&acirc;ng ngÆ°á»i l&ecirc;n chÆ°a Ä‘á»§ cao. Viá»‡c thá»±c hiá»‡n Ä‘áº§y Ä‘á»§ má»™t loáº¡t c&aacute;c chuyá»ƒn Ä‘á»™ng báº¯t Ä‘áº§u tá»« khi treo ngÆ°á»i l&ecirc;n cho Ä‘áº¿n khi cáº±m cá»§a báº¡n hÆ¡i cao hÆ¡n thanh x&agrave; sáº½ gi&uacute;p cÆ¡ thá»ƒ ph&aacute;t triá»ƒn to&agrave;n diá»‡n c&aacute;c nh&oacute;m cÆ¡ má»¥c ti&ecirc;u v&agrave; Ä‘áº¡t Ä‘Æ°á»£c hiá»‡u quáº£ tá»‘i Ä‘a cá»§a b&agrave;i táº­p.</p>\r\n<p>Äá»ƒ pháº§n cÆ¡ vai v&agrave; tay ph&aacute;t triá»ƒn máº¡nh máº½ sÄƒn cháº¯c nháº¥t, báº¡n cáº§n tu&acirc;n thá»§ Ä‘&uacute;ng nhá»¯ng nguy&ecirc;n t&aacute;c h&iacute;t x&agrave; tr&ecirc;n nh&eacute;.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="clearfix">&nbsp;</div>\r\nNguá»“n: http://www.thehinh.com/2017/01/sai-lam-hit-xa-don-cho-co-vai-va-bap-tay-san-chac.html<br />\r\n<div class="clearfix">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="shareit bottom">&nbsp;</div>', '2019-02-05 22:34:39', 'general'),
	(9, 'Chiáº¿n tháº¯ng ung thÆ° hiá»ƒm nghÃ¨o nhá» táº­p gym cá»§a chÃ ng 9x', 'dam-me-tap-gym-giup-9x-thoat-khoi-benh-ung-1.png', 'chien-thang-ung-thu-hiem-ngheo-nho-tap-gym-cua-chang-9x', '<p>Máº·c d&ugrave; ráº¥t sá»‘c khi biáº¿t m&igrave;nh bá»‹ ung thÆ° háº¡ch, nhÆ°ng nhá» &yacute; ch&iacute; ki&ecirc;n cÆ°á»ng c&ugrave;ng phÆ°Æ¡ng ph&aacute;p luyá»‡n táº­p thá»ƒ h&igrave;nh Ä‘a gi&uacute;p...</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<div class="thecontent">\r\n<h2>Máº·c d&ugrave; ráº¥t sá»‘c khi biáº¿t m&igrave;nh bá»‹ ung thÆ° háº¡ch, nhÆ°ng nhá» &yacute; ch&iacute; ki&ecirc;n cÆ°á»ng c&ugrave;ng phÆ°Æ¡ng ph&aacute;p luyá»‡n táº­p thá»ƒ h&igrave;nh Ä‘a gi&uacute;p ch&agrave;ng trai 9x chiáº¿n tháº¯ng cÄƒn bá»‡nh hiá»ƒm ngh&egrave;o má»™t c&aacute;ch ngoáº¡n má»¥c.</h2>\r\n<p><img title="" src="http://blogthehinh.net/uploads/images/10/2017/12/09/382/dam-me-tap-gym-giup-9x-thoat-khoi-benh-ung-2.png" alt="Äam m&ecirc; táº­p gym gi&uacute;p 9x tho&aacute;t khá»i bá»‡nh ung thÆ° hiá»ƒm ngh&egrave;o" /></p>\r\n<p>Äau Ä‘á»›n v&agrave; ch&aacute;n trÆ°á»ng khi pháº£i váº­t lá»™n vá»›i nhá»¯ng láº§n&nbsp;h&oacute;a trá»‹ v&agrave; ph&oacute;ng xáº¡ chá»‘ng ung thÆ°.</p>\r\n<p><img title="" src="http://blogthehinh.net/uploads/images/10/2017/12/09/382/dam-me-tap-gym-giup-9x-thoat-khoi-benh-ung-3.png" alt="Äam m&ecirc; táº­p gym gi&uacute;p 9x tho&aacute;t khá»i bá»‡nh ung thÆ° hiá»ƒm ngh&egrave;o" /></p>\r\n<p>Táº­m ch&iacute;, cáº­u c&ograve;n cháº³ng c&oacute; Ä‘á»§ sá»©c lá»±c Ä‘á»ƒ hoáº¡t Ä‘á»™ng b&igrave;nh thÆ°á»ng nhÆ° bao ngÆ°á»i m&agrave; anh chá»‰ biáº¿t náº±m má»™t chá»—, sinh nháº­t thá»© 16 cá»§a m&igrave;nh Ä‘&atilde; Ä‘Æ°á»£c tá»• chá»©c ngay táº¡i giÆ°á»ng bá»‡nh cá»§a anh.</p>\r\n<p><img title="" src="http://blogthehinh.net/uploads/images/10/2017/12/09/382/dam-me-tap-gym-giup-9x-thoat-khoi-benh-ung-4.png" alt="Äam m&ecirc; táº­p gym gi&uacute;p 9x tho&aacute;t khá»i bá»‡nh ung thÆ° hiá»ƒm ngh&egrave;o" /></p>\r\n<p>Ch&agrave;ng trai sinh nÄƒm 1994 Ä‘&atilde; kh&oacute;c tuyá»‡t vá»ng sau Ä‘á»£t xáº¡ trá»‹ Ä‘áº§u ti&ecirc;n. NHÆ°ng nhá» táº¥t cáº£ nhá»¯ng lá»i Ä‘á»™ng vi&ecirc;n cá»§a ngÆ°á»i th&acirc;n, ch&agrave;ng trai tráº» n&agrave;y Ä‘&atilde; c&oacute; th&ecirc;m Ä‘á»™ng lá»±c Ä‘á»ƒ chá»‘ng chá»i láº¡i bá»‡nh táº­t.</p>\r\n<p><img title="" src="http://blogthehinh.net/uploads/images/10/2017/12/09/382/dam-me-tap-gym-giup-9x-thoat-khoi-benh-ung-5.png" alt="Äam m&ecirc; táº­p gym gi&uacute;p 9x tho&aacute;t khá»i bá»‡nh ung thÆ° hiá»ƒm ngh&egrave;o" /></p>\r\n<p>V&igrave; tháº¿, Anh quyáº¿t Ä‘á»‹nh tham gia 1 lá»›p&nbsp;<strong>táº­p thá»ƒ h&igrave;nh</strong>&nbsp;nháº±m tÄƒng cÆ°á»ng sá»©c khá»e v&agrave; káº¿t quáº£ sau v&agrave;i nÄƒm khiáº¿n ai tá»«ng quen biáº¿t anh cÅ©ng pháº£i ngá»¡ ng&agrave;ng.</p>\r\n<p><img title="" src="http://blogthehinh.net/uploads/images/10/2017/12/09/382/dam-me-tap-gym-giup-9x-thoat-khoi-benh-ung-6.png" alt="Äam m&ecirc; táº­p gym gi&uacute;p 9x tho&aacute;t khá»i bá»‡nh ung thÆ° hiá»ƒm ngh&egrave;o" /></p>\r\n<p>Anh ch&agrave;ng lao v&agrave;o táº­p luyá»‡n luyá»‡n ngay trong thá»i gian pháº£i chá»‹u h&oacute;a trá»‹, háº±ng ng&agrave;y Zach Zeiler&nbsp;<strong>táº­p gym</strong>&nbsp;2 tiáº¿ng Ä‘á»“ng há»“.</p>\r\n<p><img title="" src="http://blogthehinh.net/uploads/images/10/2017/12/09/382/dam-me-tap-gym-giup-9x-thoat-khoi-benh-ung-7.png" alt="Äam m&ecirc; táº­p gym gi&uacute;p 9x tho&aacute;t khá»i bá»‡nh ung thÆ° hiá»ƒm ngh&egrave;o" /></p>\r\n<p>C&ugrave;ng &yacute; ch&iacute; láº¡c quan tin tÆ°á»Ÿng v&agrave;o tÆ°Æ¡ng lai&nbsp;k&egrave;m cháº¿ Ä‘á»™ dinh dÆ°á»¡ng há»£p l&yacute;, há»‡ miá»…n dá»‹ch cá»§a anh Ä‘&atilde; phá»¥c há»“i Ä‘Æ°á»£c kh&aacute; nhiá»u chá»©c nÄƒng Ä‘á» kh&aacute;ng vá»›i ung thÆ°.</p>\r\n<p><img title="" src="http://blogthehinh.net/uploads/images/10/2017/12/09/382/dam-me-tap-gym-giup-9x-thoat-khoi-benh-ung-8.png" alt="Äam m&ecirc; táº­p gym gi&uacute;p 9x tho&aacute;t khá»i bá»‡nh ung thÆ° hiá»ƒm ngh&egrave;o" /></p>\r\n<p>Sau 3 nÄƒm miá»‡t m&agrave;i khá»• luyá»‡n cÄƒn bá»‡nh ung thÆ° cá»§a anh dáº§n Ä‘Æ°á»£c Ä‘áº©y l&ugrave;i.</p>\r\n<p><img title="" src="http://blogthehinh.net/uploads/images/10/2017/12/09/382/dam-me-tap-gym-giup-9x-thoat-khoi-benh-ung-9.png" alt="Äam m&ecirc; táº­p gym gi&uacute;p 9x tho&aacute;t khá»i bá»‡nh ung thÆ° hiá»ƒm ngh&egrave;o" /></p>\r\n<p>Anh ch&agrave;ng Ä‘&atilde; &aacute;p dá»¥ng cháº¿ Ä‘á»™ dinh dÆ°á»¡ng l&ecirc;n tá»›i&nbsp;4000-5000 calo v&agrave; thá»±c hiá»‡n má»™t cháº¿ Ä‘á»™ táº­p luyá»‡n cá»±c ká»³ nghi&ecirc;m ngáº·t.</p>\r\n<p><img title="" src="http://blogthehinh.net/uploads/images/10/2017/12/09/382/dam-me-tap-gym-giup-9x-thoat-khoi-benh-ung-10.png" alt="Äam m&ecirc; táº­p gym gi&uacute;p 9x tho&aacute;t khá»i bá»‡nh ung thÆ° hiá»ƒm ngh&egrave;o" /></p>\r\n<p>Chiáº¿n tháº¯ng lu&ocirc;n d&agrave;nh cho nhá»¯ng ngÆ°á»i ki&ecirc;n tr&igrave; khá»• luyá»‡n c&ugrave;ng &yacute; ch&iacute; láº¡c quan y&ecirc;u Ä‘á»i, Anh tá»« 1 ch&agrave;ng trai gáº§y nhÆ° c&ograve; ma, chá»‰ c&oacute; 45 k&yacute; m&agrave; giá» Ä‘&acirc;y Ä‘&atilde; trá»Ÿ th&agrave;nh 1 thanh ni&ecirc;n cao 1,83m v&agrave; náº·ng 80kg. C&ugrave;ng vá»›i Ä‘&oacute; l&agrave; th&acirc;n h&igrave;nh lá»±c lÆ°á»¡ng vá»›i cÆ¡ báº¯p cuá»“n cuá»™n.</p>\r\n<p><img title="" src="http://blogthehinh.net/uploads/images/10/2017/12/09/382/dam-me-tap-gym-giup-9x-thoat-khoi-benh-ung-11.png" alt="Äam m&ecirc; táº­p gym gi&uacute;p 9x tho&aacute;t khá»i bá»‡nh ung thÆ° hiá»ƒm ngh&egrave;o" /></p>\r\n<p>V&agrave; tá»« Ä‘&oacute;, Anh ch&agrave;ng Ä‘Æ°á»£c cá»™ng Ä‘á»™ng máº¡ng háº¿t lá»i khen ngá»£i, trá»Ÿ th&agrave;nh táº¥m gÆ°Æ¡ng nghá»‹ lá»±c cho h&agrave;ng triá»‡u báº¡n tráº» kh&aacute;c Ä‘ang bá»‹ ung thÆ° v&agrave; bá»‡nh táº­t tr&ecirc;n to&agrave;n tháº¿ giá»›i.</p>\r\n<p>Äáº¿n Ä‘&acirc;y Ä‘&atilde; l&agrave; 5 nÄƒm ká»ƒ tá»« ng&agrave;y ph&aacute;t hiá»‡n Æ°ng thÆ° v&agrave; Zach Ä‘&atilde; khá»i háº³n bá»‡nh táº­t Ä‘á»“ng thá»i anh sá»Ÿ há»¯u th&acirc;n h&igrave;nh l&yacute; tÆ°á»Ÿng cá»§a biáº¿t bao gymer kh&aacute;c c&ugrave;ng cuá»™c sá»‘ng háº¡nh ph&uacute;c.</p>\r\n<p><img title="" src="http://blogthehinh.net/uploads/images/10/2017/12/09/382/dam-me-tap-gym-giup-9x-thoat-khoi-benh-ung-12.png" alt="Äam m&ecirc; táº­p gym gi&uacute;p 9x tho&aacute;t khá»i bá»‡nh ung thÆ° hiá»ƒm ngh&egrave;o" /></p>\r\n<p>Nhá» qu&aacute; tr&igrave;nh táº­p luyá»‡n c&ugrave;ng kiáº¿n thá»©c dinh dÆ°á»¡ng c&oacute; Ä‘Æ°á»£c n&ecirc;n giá» anh Ä‘ang&nbsp;l&agrave;m huáº¥n luyá»‡n vi&ecirc;n thá»ƒ h&igrave;nh chuy&ecirc;n nghiá»‡p. Anh quáº£ tháº­t l&agrave; 1 táº¥m gÆ°Æ¡ng vÆ°á»£t l&ecirc;n sá»± kh&oacute; khÄƒn m&agrave; táº¥t cáº£ c&aacute;c báº¡n tráº» cáº§n pháº£i há»c táº­p.</p>\r\n<p><img title="" src="http://blogthehinh.net/uploads/images/10/2017/12/09/382/dam-me-tap-gym-giup-9x-thoat-khoi-benh-ung-13.png" alt="Äam m&ecirc; táº­p gym gi&uacute;p 9x tho&aacute;t khá»i bá»‡nh ung thÆ° hiá»ƒm ngh&egrave;o" /></p>\r\n<p>Nhá»¯ng h&igrave;nh áº£nh táº­p luyá»‡n Ä‘Æ°á»£c Zach chia sáº» háº±ng ng&agrave;y tr&ecirc;n trang c&aacute; nh&acirc;n cá»§a anh cÅ©ng l&agrave; nguá»“n Ä‘á»™ng lá»±c cho nhá»¯ng&nbsp;ai Ä‘ang ng&agrave;y Ä‘&ecirc;m chá»‘ng chá»i vá»›i bá»‡nh táº­t.</p>\r\n<p><img title="" src="http://blogthehinh.net/uploads/images/10/2017/12/09/382/dam-me-tap-gym-giup-9x-thoat-khoi-benh-ung-14.png" alt="Äam m&ecirc; táº­p gym gi&uacute;p 9x tho&aacute;t khá»i bá»‡nh ung thÆ° hiá»ƒm ngh&egrave;o" /></p>\r\n<p>Zach t&acirc;m sá»±: &ldquo;T&ocirc;i cáº£m tháº¥y tháº­t may máº¯n v&agrave; háº¡nh ph&uacute;c, t&ocirc;i sáº½ kh&ocirc;ng dá»«ng láº¡i v&agrave; tiáº¿p tá»¥c truyá»n cáº£m há»©ng cho nhiá»u ngÆ°á»i hÆ¡n ná»¯a.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Zach chia sáº» lá»‹ch táº­p luyá»‡n cá»§a anh trong suá»‘t thá»i gian qua:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Thá»© 2: Ngá»±c/Tay sau</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; Dumbbell Pullover: 3&times;12,10,6 &ndash; Incline Dumbbell Press: 4&times;12.10,8,6 &ndash; Flat Dumbbell Press: 4&times;12,10,8,6 &ndash; Decline Isolateral Machine Press: 3&times;10 &ndash; Dumbbell Fly&rsquo;s: 3&times;10-15 &ndash; Cable Crossovers: 3&times;10-15 &ndash; Overhead Dumbbell Extension: 4&times;12,10,8,6 &ndash; Overhead Single Arm Triceps Extension: 3&times;10 &ndash; Dumbbell Triceps Skull Crushers: 4&times;10 &ndash; Single Arm Cable Triceps Pushdown: 3&times;10</li>\r\n<li><strong>Thá»© 3: Ch&acirc;n</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; Squats: 5 working sets 14.12.10,8,6 (last set a dropset) &ndash; Hack squat: 4&times;12,10,8,6 &ndash; Leg Press: 4&times;10-14 &ndash; Leg Extensions: 4&times;10-20 &ndash; Laying Leg Curl: 4&times;8-12 &ndash; Stiff Leg Dumbbell Deadlift: 4&times;12,10,8,6 &ndash; Standing Leg Curl: 4&times;10</li>\r\n<li><strong>Thá»© 4: LÆ°ng/ Tay trÆ°á»›c</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; Lat Pulldown: 4&times;8-12 &ndash; Isolateral Lat Pulldown: 4&times;8-12 &ndash; Pull-ups: 2x failure &ndash; T-Bar Row: 4&times;10 &ndash; One Arm Dumbbell Row: 4&times;12,10,8,6 &ndash; Isolateral Row: 3&times;10 &ndash; Cable Row: 4&times;10-15 &ndash; Barbell Curl: 4&times;20-30 &ndash; Dumbbell Alternating Curl: 3-4&times;20-30 &ndash; One Arm Preacher Curl: 4&times;15-20</li>\r\n<li><strong>Thá»© 5: Vai</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; Reverse Pec Dec (Rear Delts): 3&times;15 &ndash; Rear Delts Cable Fly: 4&times;10 &ndash; Dumbbell Shoulder Press: 5&times;14.12,10,8,6 &ndash; Side Lateral Raise: 4&times;8-12 &ndash; Upright Row: 3&times;10 &ndash; Single Arm Side Lateral Raise: 3&times;10 &ndash; Dumbbell Front Raise: 3&times;8-12 &ndash; Isolateral Shoulder Press: 4&times;10 &ndash; Barbell Shrugs: 6&times;20,16,12,10,8,6 (last set a dropset) &ndash; Dumbbell Shrugs: 5&times;10</li>\r\n<li><strong>Thá»© 6: Ngá»±c/Tay sau</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; Dumbbell Pullover: 3&times;10 &ndash; Barbell Bench Press: 4&times;12,10,8,6 (last set a dropset) &ndash; Incline Isolateral Bench: 4&times;12,10,8,6 &ndash; Cable Crossover: 4&times;10 &ndash; Pec Dec Fly: 4&times;10 &ndash; Weighted Dips: 4&times;12,10,8,6 &ndash; Barbell Skull Crushers: 4&times;12,10,8,6 &ndash; Cable Overhead Triceps Extension: 3&times;10 &ndash; Rope Triceps Pushdown: 3&times;20</li>\r\n<li><strong>Thá»© 7: Ch&acirc;n</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; Leg Extensions: 4&times;10 &ndash; Squats: 5&times;5 &ndash; Hack squat/Lunges Superset: 4&times;10 &ndash; Sissy Squats: 4&times;15 &ndash; Single Leg Hamstring Curls: 4&times;10 &ndash; Reverse Hack Squats: 4&times;10 &ndash; Barbell SL Deadlifts: 3&times;12,10,8 &ndash; Laying Leg Curl: 3x to failure</li>\r\n<li><strong>Chá»§ nháº­t: LÆ°ng/ Tay trÆ°á»›c</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; Deadlifts: 6&times;20,14,12,10,8,6 &ndash; Barbell Row: 4&times;12,10,8,6 &ndash; Wide Grip Cable Row: 3&times;10 &ndash; One Arm Dumbbell Row: 3&times;10 &ndash; Unilateral Row: 3&times;10 &ndash; Weighted Pullups: 3&times;10 &ndash; Dumbbell Pullover: 3&times;8 &ndash; Close Grip Lat Pulldown: 3&times;10 &ndash; Dumbbell Hammer Curl (One Arm): 4&times;20-30 &ndash; Concentration Curl: 4&times;20 &ndash; Preacher Curl: 3&times;20 &ndash; Cable Curl: 2&times;30</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Trong c&aacute;c b&agrave;i táº­p gym n&agrave;y th&igrave; Zach th&iacute;ch nháº¥t 3 b&agrave;i:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>B&agrave;i táº­p Bench Dumbbell Press</strong>: Anh cho biáº¿t Ä‘&acirc;y l&agrave; b&agrave;i táº­p gi&uacute;p ngá»±c m&igrave;nh ph&aacute;t triá»ƒn tá»‘t nháº¥t v&agrave; c&aacute;c báº¡n cÅ©ng n&ecirc;n Æ°u ti&ecirc;n b&agrave;i n&agrave;y nhiá»u hÆ¡n.</li>\r\n<li><strong>B&agrave;i táº­p Squat</strong>: Máº·c d&ugrave; chauw bá» lá»¡ 1 ng&agrave;y táº­p ch&acirc;n n&agrave;o nhÆ°ng pháº£i máº¥t 1 nÄƒm th&igrave; Zack má»›i c&oacute; thá»ƒ th&agrave;nh thá»¥c Ä‘á»™ng t&aacute;c n&agrave;y, anh cho biáº¿t Squat ch&iacute;nh l&agrave; b&iacute; máº­t cho Ä‘&ocirc;i ch&acirc;n cá»§a anh hiá»‡n nay.</li>\r\n<li><strong>B&agrave;i táº­p Deadlift</strong>: Ä&acirc;y cÅ©ng l&agrave; má»™t b&agrave;i táº­p cáº­u táº­p kh&aacute; trá»…, Ä‘&oacute; l&agrave; nÄƒm thá»© 3 v&igrave; cáº­u áº¥y sá»£ kh&ocirc;n